$interpreted: Tindoiimu: Juan-Yun, you're alive!? How!?
Tindoiimu: Butter!?
Juan-Yun: Be good, Butter, let me talk to the princess first.
Tindoiimu: What happened? That power... the spirit wind...
Juan-Yun: Where should I start...
Juan-Yun: Honestly, I just wish it never came to this. Because now, things will have to get... explosive~
Juan-Yun: Are you ready for the grand finale, Princess?
Tingko: Princess, watch out!
Juan-Yun: ...Do you want to take her place? Fine with me!
Tindoiimu: Ting... ko...
Juan-Yun: Injecting your poisonous insect blood here will weaken the seal, awaken the Monster of Judgement!
Tindoiimu: What have you done to Tingko!?
Juan-Yun: She has returned to the Insect Tribe's source...
Tindoiimu: What... the source?
Juan-Yun: ...Fine, I suppose I can fill you in. Everything's finished now, anyhow.
Juan-Yun: A long time ago, there was a Monster of Judgement. It sucked up all of this world's Mythic Energy and turned it into a poison, ravaging the east.
Juan-Yun: The Immortals were powerless against it, so they created the Udumbara as a way to absorb this poison.
Juan-Yun: The Udumbara and the Monster intertwined, creating this huge tree. It blocked up the void, just like the Holy Dragon.
Juan-Yun: With the poison gone, these beautiful eastern lands flourished once again.
Juan-Yun: Or so we thought... In reality, the poison couldn't be abated so easily. It seeped through the earth, finally creating the Insect Tribe.
Tindoiimu: ...The Insect Tribe...?
Juan-Yun: That's right. You were born from that very poison.
Tindoiimu: But now... Tingko... How can we bring Tingko back!?
Juan-Yun: Tingko...?
Juan-Yun: Yeah, looks like it might have to be you...
Tindoiimu: What are you talking about!? Just bring Tingko back to me!!
Juan-Yun: When are you going to stop lying to yourself?
Juan-Yun: Tingko's never coming back!
Tindoiimu: Don't say that...
Juan-Yun: That's why it's said that when insect blood sullies eastern soil,
Juan-Yun: the Udumbara will start to flower, as if sucking up some kind of lifeblood. More blood, more flowers.
Tindoiimu: Blood...!? So... you just...
Tindoiimu: No! You're not the real Juan-Yun!
Tindoiimu: The real Juan-Yun might be a bit unrealistic, but he's righteous! He only cares about his family and about peace!
Juan-Yun: And yet I am Juan-Yun. But at the same time, I'm also...
Juan-Yun: First Parhelion of the Dracontines.
Juan-Yun: It's true, family and peace are my first priorities, but my home... my home is wherever Sdorica resides.
Juan-Yun: Unfortunately, the Udumbara's barrier made it difficult for us to gain access for all of these years.
Juan-Yun: Even if one of us became arbiter, we couldn't just bring an insect in here. That's why we had to assure an insect won the tournament.
Tindoiimu: Y-You're lying... You brought up Himawari like she was part of your real family, and she wasn't part of the Insect Tribe...
Juan-Yun: Himawari? Can you really not recognize one of your own, oh fallen princess?
Tindoiimu: Himawari... she was from the Insect Tribe!?
Juan-Yun: She was an orphan. I found her out on her own while researching insect ruins.
Juan-Yun: She was very young, didn't even know what the Insect Tribe was. She wasn't difficult to raise up as one of our own.
Juan-Yun: That said, I often worried her blood wasn't pure enough to awaken the monster.
Juan-Yun: But then I met you. A pureblooded insect princess.
Tindoiimu: So... Himawari and I... we were just your pawns?
Juan-Yun: Sure, but that doesn't mean I don't care about you.
Juan-Yun: My feelings for you have been true, to both of you.
Juan-Yun: And I truly am sorry for any harm I've brought to your people.
Tindoiimu: Y-You're the one who bribed Baa-Baa at Hot Spring Street! Aren't you!?
Juan-Yun: ……
Tindoiimu: You also left way earlier than everyone else... There's no way you would have gotten to Hot Spring Street before the Alliance did, unless you never really went home!
Tindoiimu: You were in cahoots with Baa-Baa!
Juan-Yun: It's all because...
Tindoiimu: Shut up! I'm tired of your lies!
Juan-Yun: Tindoiimu, I've never lied to you. You've only lied to yourself.
Juan-Yun: I always told you that you were my second priority.
Tindoiimu: You...!
Tindoiimu: Yagh... mgh... why...
Juan-Yun: I'm sorry, but if I want to get back home, I need your blood.
Tindoiimu: Agh... Yaaagh!!
Tindoiimu: Yaaaaaaagggghh!!
Juan-Yun: It is finished...
Tindoiimu: Gugh... Juan... Yun...
Juan-Yun: ...Thank Sdorica you're still alive... I'd almost given up all hope...
Juan-Yun: Yagh!
Tindoiimu: ...You... can't...
Juan-Yun: Princess... let go...
Tindoiimu: I... still haven't...
Juan-Yun: Run away, Princess. Run far away from here.
Juan-Yun: I'll always be waiting for you. But don't come and find me.
Tindoiimu: The look on your face... mngh... why... you're in more pain than I am...
Juan-Yun: Take care of yourself, Princess. I had a wonderful time... mngh... being Juan-Yun... with you...
Tindoiimu: Wait...
